Needs + infinite + passive

We can give instruction using needs + infinite + the passive form in situations when we don't know who is going to do
it, or it's not important who is going to do it.

Remember that passive forms of verbs include the verb be + past particle.

It needs to be done.

The report needs to be completed this week.

All homework needs to be handed in after class.

The project doesn't need to be finished quickly.

The wall needs to be built by the end od tomorrow.

The meal needs to be cooked by 5:00 pm.

The packages don't need to be mailed today.

What needs to be done? 
The report needs to be written.
